Mohan,

Generally, this is tackled using the Parameterized Test Case pattern.  It&#39;s
described well in Rainsberger&#39;s book &quot;JUnit Recipes&quot;, but here&#39;s a recent
example from the list (thanks, Elliotte).  Share and Enjoy,

   David Saff

import junit.framework.*;
import junit.textui.TestRunner;

public class DataDrivenTest extends TestCase{

int i;

public DataDrivenTest(int i) {
  super(&quot;testFoo&quot;);
  this.i = i;
}

public static Test suite() {
  TestSuite result = new TestSuite();
  result.addTest(new DataDrivenTest(1));
  result.addTest(new DataDrivenTest(2));
  result.addTest(new DataDrivenTest(3));
  return result;
}


public void testFoo() {
  assertTrue(i &gt; 0);
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
  TestRunner.run(suite());
}
}

